Member 1 – Database + Core Setup
Role: Build the foundation
Tasks:
Design and create all tables in PostgreSQL
Define relationships (FK constraints)
Insert sample data
Set up database connection in PHP (config.php)
Write basic reusable queries
Also helps with:
Debugging DB-related issues

Member 2 – Student Module (PHP + UI)
Role: Complete student management
Tasks:
Add Student (form + PHP)
View Students (table display)
Update Student
Delete Student
Connect frontend form to backend
👉 This is a full CRUD module

Member 3 – Course + Enrollment Module
Role: Handle course logic
Tasks:
Add/View/Update/Delete Courses
Enroll students into courses
Display enrolled students per course
Use JOIN queries (important learning part)

Member 4 – Attendance + Grades Module
Role: Academic tracking features
Tasks:
Mark attendance (Present/Absent)
View attendance records
Enter marks & assign grades
Display results

Shared Responsibility (Everyone Must Do)
All members should:
Use same database structure
Follow same naming conventions
Test their module independently

Integration Plan (VERY IMPORTANT)
At the end:
Combine all modules into:
dashboard.php
Ensure navigation works between pages
Fix errors (everyone participates)
👉 Don’t leave integration to one person—it will break.

